obfuscation: So long, and well what is up right now, and putting-- putting, and anna, and hello-- father, and she told me it was you, and i must got here a little while ago, it 's good-- for see you-- following all dem years Anna, it 's nice to see so do you, anna villa; anna villa!
original: So long. Well, what's up now? Nutting--nutting. Anna! Hello--father. She told me it was you. I yust got here a little while ago. It's good--for see you--after all dem years, Anna. It's good to see you, too. Anna lilla! Anna lilla!

obfuscation: Yet, What 's that-- Swedish, and i do n't know it; and gee I had an awful trip coming here, and i 'm all in; i had to sit up inside the dirty coach all night-- could not get no sleep hardly-- and then I had a hard job finding this place.
original: What's that--Swedish? I don't know it. Gee, I had an awful trip coming here. I'm all in. I had to sit up in the dirty coach all night--couldn't get no sleep, hardly--and then I had a hard job finding this place.

obfuscation: I never been of New York before you know and-- You acknowledge you vas awful booty freezing Anna; and ay bet all men see you fall of love with you by aiming; and cut it; and you talk same as they all do.
original: I never been in New York before, you know, and--   You know you vas awful pooty gel, Anna? Ay bet all men see you fall in love with you, py yiminy! Cut it! You talk same as they all do.

obfuscation: Obviously, Ai n't no harm for your faded speak dat may Anna; no-- course not, as only-- it is funny to understand you again and not recall anything; and you are like-- an alien; as ay s'pose; ay never come home only few times men you vas kit of sweden.
original: Ain't no harm for your fader talk dat vay, Anna. No--course not. Only--it's funny to see you and not remember nothing. You're like--a stranger. Ay s'pose. Ay never come home only few times ven you vas kit in Sveden.

obfuscation: You do n't remember dat, no; as but why did n't you never come home them days, and why did not you never come out West to understand me?
original: You don't remember dat? No. But why didn't you never come home them days? Why didn't you never come out West to see me?

obfuscation: Ay tank after your mo would die men Ay vas away on voyage it 's best for you you do not never understand me; as [ He sinks down inside the presidency opposite her dejected-- then turns to her-- sadly. ]
original: Ay tank, after your mo'der die, ven Ay vas avay on voyage, it's better for you you don't never see me! [He sinks down in the chair opposite her dejectedly--then turns to her--sadly.]

obfuscation: Ay do n't know Anna why Ay never come home sweden of ole year; ay want come dwelling conclusion of each voyage; ay want see your mo'der your two brow harder before dey vas drowned you men you vas born-- but-- Ay-- do not go.
original: Ay don't know, Anna, vhy Ay never come home Sveden in ole year. Ay vant come home end of every voyage. Ay vant see your mo'der, your two bro'der before dey vas drowned, you ven you vas born--but--Ay--don't go.

obfuscation: Ay sign on oder ships-- go South America go Australia travel China go each port all over international many times-- but Ay never go aboard ship sail for sweden, men Ay at money for pay passage home as passenger den-- Ay forget and Ay spend all money.
original: Ay sign on oder ships--go South America, go Australia, go China, go every port all over world many times--but Ay never go aboard ship sail for Sveden. Ven Ay gat money for pay passage home as passenger den-- Ay forgat and Ay spend all money.

obfuscation: men Ay tank again it 's too late, ay do not know why but dat 's may with the majority sailor fall Anna, and dat ole devil sea make dem crazy fools with her dirty tricks; and it 's so.
original: Ven Ay tank again, it's too late. Ay don't know vhy but dat's vay with most sailor fallar, Anna. Dat ole davil sea make dem crazy fools with her dirty tricks. It's so.
